product1 = 'facecream'
product2 = 'facewash'

comparison_df = data[['month_number', product1, product2]]

comparison_df.plot(x='month_number', kind='bar', figsize=(10, 6))
plt.title('  {}  {}  '.format(product1, product2))
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylabel(' ')
plt.xticks(rotation=0)
plt.legend(loc='upper left')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

#     
#       
correlation_profit = data.corr()['total_profit'].drop(
    ['month_number', 'total_units', 'total_profit'])

#     
#      
fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=3, figsize=(15, 10))

for idx, (product, ax) in enumerate(
        zip(correlation_profit.index, axes.flatten())):
    ax.scatter(df[product], df['total_profit'], alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_title(': {:.2f}'.format(correlation_profit[idx]))
    ax.set_xlabel(' {}'.format(product))
    ax.set_ylabel(' ')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

print("  :")
print(correlation_profit)
